post_text:
Class of 2020 Graduation Update:

I want to start by saying a huge thank you to all that participated in the senior parade. It was awesome! Below you will find an update on Graduation. I‚Äôm trying really hard to have something for the seniors but we have to follow the Health Department and Governor.

The graduation window will be from Thursday 6/25 to Saturday 6/27. Our plan is to give individual diplomas to students in an outdoor setting (hopefully on the new turf field). We have the window to allow for any unfavorable weather. If guidance from the health department changes the individual ceremonies would be moved inside or a possibly larger class group outside. We are waiting until 6/19 to determine final plan based on guidance from Health Department.

In any scenario at this point would not include crowds or spectators. At this point it will be immediate family only.

I know there are not exact details yet but the situation changes daily. In any event I want to have something for you. You all deserve it.

Stay safe and stay tuned‚Ä¶..

Miss all of you!

post_text: Our Gator Family misses all of you! We are trying to stay connected with our students during the difficult times. Hopefully we see you sooner then later.
text: Our Gator Family misses all of you! We are trying to stay connected with our students during the difficult times. Hopefully we see you sooner then later.

post_text:
Good afternoon, I would like to update all our families and students. Our building is still in a "hard close" which means no students or faculty can enter the building. We are working very hard to get instructional materials out of lockers and food delivered to our families. I would like to thank our office staff who have fielded hundreds of calls and our support staff for running the hallways trying to get supplies to students. This really is a Gator family working together.

I would like to thank you and ask for your continued patience as we navigate uncharted waters.

In a continued effort to keep all of us safe, we have reduced the working hours our essential staff are working. Starting today and continuing until further notice, the MHS office will be open from 9:30 am until 2:00 pm.

Please contact the office with any questions and ask your students to check their school email.

Please be safe and take care of each other.

Mr. Pecorella
This Gator Family Rocks!

Michael Wilber Sr. is with Jon Luce and 11 others at Kerr-Pegula Athletic Complex.
February 22 at 8:39 PM ¬∑ Houghton, NY ¬∑

Section 6 Indoor Track and Field Championships.
Congratulations to our Gators... what a day!
Michael Wolfgang won the 55 Hurdles (7.84) and won the High Jump (6-0) and also was awarded the MVP from Team Championships.
Liam Coulter finished second in the 55Hurdles (7.94).
Our girls 4 x 400 (Angelina Napoleon, Ashlyn Collins, Jackie Daley, Marina Miketish)was third overall (4:11.92 - our best time of the season, dropped 7 seconds today)after a close finish among the top 3 teams. Freshman Angelina Napoleon also finished third in the High Jump (5-1), Junior Jackie Daley was sixth in the 300 (44.74), senior Marina Miketish was 7th in High Jump (4-10) and 13th in the 55 Hurdles (9.73), eighth grader Tyyetta Herman finished 9th on the 600 (1:43.77) and freshman Ashlyn Collins was 10th (1:44.78). Sophomores Jacob Brink 3200 - (10:32) and Daniel Casey 1600 (5:02) finished 12th and 19th respectively.
GATOR PRIDE!!!

post_text:
Parents/Guardians...as I stood outside this morning greeting the students I saw several students get off the bus and out of cars with no jacket on and in a few cases shorts and a t-shirt. The temperature was somewhere around 14 degrees. I heard several students say "I'm only outside for a minute before I go in". That is a true statement...however if we ever need to evacuate for any reason (heat stops working, fire alarm, etc.) students will be standing outside for a while. Having 2 teenage girls I do understand the struggle. Please, please for their safety and security have them wear a jacket and appropriate clothing during these cold temperatures. We don't want anything to happen to our students.

We have a clothes closet in the MHS if any student is in need of appropriate clothing. Please contact the main office or the students counselor.

Have a nice long weekend and stay warm.

Allegany-Limestone Elementary School
January 6 at 5:53 PM ¬∑

The Allegany-Limestone Board of Education and our District Leadership Team have worked hard to ensure the items in this project will support our mission to provide our students with access and opportunities for a well-rounded school experience. We understand that our school facilities serve an important role to our community as a place where families and townspeople come together. Over time, items need to be replaced, repaired, or upgraded to meet the many needs of our students, families, and community members.

There will be a PUBLIC INFORMATIONAL MEETING - JAN 14, 2020 at 6 PM IN THE ELEMENTARY MULTI-PURPOSE ROOM.

shared_text:
Michael Wilber Sr. is with Jon Luce and 7 others at Kerr-Pegula Athletic Complex.
January 4 at 10:42 PM ¬∑ Instagram ¬∑

Allegany-Limestone Indoor Track and Field New Year‚Äôs Classic at Houghton College today. Liam Coulter placed first overall in the 55 Hurdles (7.84) and was sixth in the 300 (38.05).
The girls were led by a first place finish in the 4 x 400 Relay (4:21.34). Relay team of Jackie Daley, Ashlyn Collins, Marina Mikitesh and Angelina Napoleon.
Angelina also placed third in the High Jump (5-0) and fifth in the 1500 (5:13.60). Also for the girls, Ashlyn Collins finished sixth in the 600 (1:47.98).
In addition, several Gators met the Section 6 standard for the state qualifier... Liam Coulter (55H, 300), Marina Mikitesh (55H), Ashlyn Collins (600), Angelina Napoleon (1500, HJ) with several others coming close to reaching those standards or hitting their PR.
Congratulations Gators!
#ALTF
#algatortrackandfield
#ALLeganyLimestONE @ Kerr-Pegula Athletic Complex
